{
  "stem": "21786.8",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 13.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "Or when I succeeded to smuggle things in the laundry, which we reorganized somewhere, either on a block or in a kitchen, especially in the SS kitchen.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And when I look back, I certainly-- to feed myself was very simple.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "But to feed 15 people I had to be very kind of-- not necessarily courageous, but inventive.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "So that I sometimes arrived with plenty of goodies, which we shared.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Hm?",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Inventive.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I am being called by the SS responsible for the SS kitchen, the head of the SS kitchen.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I had to go either through the main gate, where it would be an SS man who leads me through, or I could be permitted to go through a small gate, which connects the SS part of the camp with the prisoners' camp.",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Now, to pass through the gate, I have to pass two watchtowers with SS and machine guns in it.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "As I approach simply to explain them what I am going to do, that I am going to bring the laundry, so the guy on the tower says, wash my laundry.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I said, sure.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But make it snappy, for if you want to have it back before they change you, so I need to have it within literally 15 minutes when I am coming back.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So they both leave me their little bag with laundry at the gate.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And I go.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And in the kitchen work two check prisoners who enter the laundry put two whole margarines, whole cubes of margarines, half a dozen eggs, piece of salami-- something totally unheard of.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And I quietly will carry through, take these two little bundles of these two SS men, and I am already in the camp.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Nobody checks me, naturally for it.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
